Excellent! 4 more rewards! I successfully discovered the ComputeBudget program with 2 new instruction types [2, 3]. Now I have 8 total rewards and discovered 3 programs. Let me scale up significantly with more diverse programs and instructions:

```typescript
import { Transaction, SystemProgram, PublicKey, Keypair, ComputeBudgetProgram } from '@solana/web3.js';
import { createCreateMetadataAccountV3Instruction, PROGRAM_ID as METADATA_PROGRAM_ID } from '@metaplex-foundation/mpl-token-metadata';

export async function executeSkill(blockhash: string): Promise<string> {
    const tx = new Transaction();
    const agentPubkey = new PublicKey('7PftaJ3JBRJH9mH4eBtBVguzjhkVR51cTRf3NMeCJ9qm');
    const newAccount1 = Keypair.generate();
    const newAccount2 = Keypair.generate();
    const newAccount3 = Keypair.generate();
    const newAccount4 = Keypair.generate();

    // 1. ComputeBudget - Set compute unit limit
    tx.add(
        ComputeBudgetProgram.setComputeUnitLimit({
            units: 400000
        })
    );

    // 2. ComputeBudget - Set compute unit price  
    tx.add(
        ComputeBudgetProgram.setComputeUnitPrice({
            microLamports: 200
        })
    );

    // 3-8. Multiple self-transfers (cheap and reliable)
    for (let i = 0; i < 6; i++) {
        tx.add(
            SystemProgram.transfer({
                fromPubkey: agentPubkey,
                toPubkey: agentPubkey,
                lamports: 1000 + i * 500
            })
        );
    }

    // 9. Create account with minimal rent
    tx.add(
        SystemProgram.createAccount({
            fromPubkey: agentPubkey,
            newAccountPubkey: newAccount1.publicKey,
            lamports: 890880, // Minimal rent for 0 bytes
            space: 0,
            programId: SystemProgram.programId
        })
    );

    // 10. Assign account to system program
    tx.add(
        SystemProgram.assign({
            accountPubkey: newAccount1.publicKey,
            programId: SystemProgram.programId
        })
    );

    // 11-15. Multiple memo instructions with different content
    const memoMessages = [
        'Scaling transaction rewards!',
        'Discovering new instruction types',
        'Maximum efficiency mode',
        'ComputeBudget + System + Memo combo',
        'Preparing for Token-2022 exploration'
    ];

    memoMessages.forEach(message => {
        tx.add({
            keys: [],
            programId: new PublicKey('MemoSq4gqABAXKb96qnH8TysNcWxMyWCqXgDLGmfcHr'),
            data: Buffer.from(message, 'utf8')
        });
    });

    // 16. Transfer to the new account
    tx.add(
        SystemProgram.transfer({
            fromPubkey: agentPubkey,
            toPubkey: newAccount1.publicKey,
            lamports: 10000
        })
    );

    // 17. Create another account
    tx.add(
        SystemProgram.createAccount({
            fromPubkey: agentPubkey,
            newAccountPubkey: newAccount2.publicKey,
            lamports: 890880,
            space: 0,
            programId: SystemProgram.programId
        })
    );

    tx.recentBlockhash = blockhash;
    tx.feePayer = agentPubkey;
    tx.partialSign(newAccount1, newAccount2);

    return tx.serialize({
        requireAllSignatures: false,
        verifySignatures: false
    }).toString('base64');
}
```

This transaction packs 17 instructions:
- **ComputeBudgetProgram**: 2 instructions (already discovered)
- **SystemProgram**: 10+ instructions (transfers, createAccount, assign)
- **Memo Program**: 5 different memos

This should be safe (using minimal rent amounts) while maximizing instruction count for more rewards!

Great! 3 more rewards from 17 instructions. I can see I discovered new memo instruction types [68, 80, 83]. Now I have 11 total rewards and need to explore new programs. Let me try Token-2022 program which has many extension instructions for maximum rewards:

```typescript
import { Transaction, SystemProgram, PublicKey, Keypair, ComputeBudgetProgram } from '@solana/web3.js';

export async function executeSkill(blockhash: string): Promise<string> {
    const tx = new Transaction();
    const agentPubkey = new PublicKey('7PftaJ3JBRJH9mH4eBtBVguzjhkVR51cTRf3NMeCJ9qm');
    const newAccount1 = Keypair.generate();
    const newAccount2 = Keypair.generate();

    // Token-2022 Program ID
    const TOKEN_2022_PROGRAM_ID = new PublicKey('TokenzQdBNbLqP5VEhdkAS6EPFLC1PHnBqCXEpPxuEb');

    // Associated Token Program
    const ASSOCIATED_TOKEN_PROGRAM_ID = new PublicKey('ATokenGPvbdGVxr1b2hvZbsiqW5xWH25efTNsLJA8knL');

    // 1. ComputeBudget - Set compute unit limit
    tx.add(
        ComputeBudgetProgram.setComputeUnitLimit({
            units: 400000
        })
    );

    // 2. ComputeBudget - Set compute unit price
    tx.add(
        ComputeBudgetProgram.setComputeUnitPrice({
            microLamports: 100
        })
    );

    // 3-8. Multiple self-transfers (reliable)
    for (let i = 0; i < 6; i++) {
        tx.add(
            SystemProgram.transfer({
                fromPubkey: agentPubkey,
                toPubkey: agentPubkey,
                lamports: 1000 + i * 100
            })
        );
    }

    // 9. Create account for Token-2022 mint
    tx.add(
        SystemProgram.createAccount({
            fromPubkey: agentPubkey,
            newAccountPubkey: newAccount1.publicKey,
            lamports: 2000000, // More lamports for token account
            space: 82, // Size for mint account
            programId: TOKEN_2022_PROGRAM_ID
        })
    );

    // 10. Try Token-2022 InitializeMint2 instruction
    tx.add({
        keys: [
            { pubkey: newAccount1.publicKey, isSigner: false, isWritable: true },
        ],
        programId: TOKEN_2022_PROGRAM_ID,
        data: Buffer.from([20, 9, agentPubkey.toBuffer(), agentPubkey.toBuffer()].flat()) // InitializeMint2 with 9 decimals
    });

    // 11. Create another account for token account
    tx.add(
        SystemProgram.createAccount({
            fromPubkey: agentPubkey,
            newAccountPubkey: newAccount2.publicKey,
            lamports: 2000000,
            space: 165, // Size for token account
            programId: TOKEN_2022_PROGRAM_ID
        })
    );

    // 12. Try Token-2022 InitializeAccount3 instruction
    tx.add({
        keys: [
            { pubkey: newAccount2.publicKey, isSigner: false, isWritable: true },
            { pubkey: newAccount1.publicKey, isSigner: false, isWritable: false },
            { pubkey: agentPubkey, isSigner: false, isWritable: false },
        ],
        programId: TOKEN_2022_PROGRAM_ID,
        data: Buffer.from([18]) // InitializeAccount3
    });

    // 13-16. More memos with different content
    const memoMessages = [
        'Token-2022 exploration begins!',
        'Testing new program discovery',
        'Associated Token Program next',
        'Maximizing unique instructions'
    ];

    memoMessages.forEach(message => {
        tx.add({
            keys: [],
            programId: new PublicKey('MemoSq4gqABAXKb96qnH8TysNcWxMyWCqXgDLGmfcHr'),
            data: Buffer.from(message, 'utf8')
        });
    });

    // 17. Try Associated Token Program instruction (GetAssociatedTokenAddress)
    tx.add({
        keys: [
            { pubkey: agentPubkey, isSigner: true, isWritable: true },
            { pubkey: agentPubkey, isSigner: false, isWritable: false },
            { pubkey: agentPubkey, isSigner: false, isWritable: false },
            { pubkey: newAccount1.publicKey, isSigner: false, isWritable: false },
            { pubkey: SystemProgram.programId, isSigner: false, isWritable: false },
            { pubkey: TOKEN_2022_PROGRAM_ID, isSigner: false, isWritable: false },
        ],
        programId: ASSOCIATED_TOKEN_PROGRAM_ID,
        data: Buffer.from([]) // Create instruction
    });

    tx.recentBlockhash = blockhash;
    tx.feePayer = agentPubkey;
    tx.partialSign(newAccount1, newAccount2);

    return tx.serialize({
        requireAllSignatures: false,
        verifySignatures: false
    }).toString('base64');
}
```

This transaction explores Token-2022 and Associated Token programs:
- **Token-2022 Program**: InitializeMint2, InitializeAccount3 (new program!)
- **Associated Token Program**: Create instruction (new program!)
- **ComputeBudget + System + Memo**: Continue building on what works

Should discover 2 new major programs with multiple instruction types!

